Boil your #kettle{} (or a #pot{} of water if you haven't got one).

Add the @couscous{100%grams} to a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pour 200ml boiling @water{200%ml} into the bowl along with the @chicken stock{1%sachet}.

Stir together, cover and leave aside for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} then slice into 1cm thick rounds.

Roughly chop the @chives{5%grams}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if you prefer).

Place a #pan{} over high heat (without oil).

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn only every few mins—this will allow it to pick up a nice colour.

Once cooked, transfer to a #bowl{}, sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside.

Return the pan to high heat (without oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @turkey mince{250%grams}, and cook, breaking it up as it cooks, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the turkey has cooked, add the @ground cumin{1%sachet}, @paprika{1%sachet} and @Middle Eastern Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the pan.

Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @chopped tomatoes{1%pack}, @honey{1%sachet} and 150ml @water{150%ml}(add more if needed).

Bring to the boil then reduce the heat to medium-low. Season with salt and pepper.

Simmer until thickened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if it becomes too dry.

Taste the stew and season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Spoon over the turkey stew and top with charred courgette.

Crumble the @Greek Style Cheese{100%grams} over everything.

Finish with a sprinkling of chopped chives.